caption: Love this place. Great staff, really solid food, drinks are always flowing. Best place to watch ACC sports in Chicago! Once we can DO sports again 😔
Bad experiences.  I was drunk and the bartender started attacking me. I'm from out of town.  Never spend your money here
Fun times and chill place to just drink and have fun

College bar that doubles as a club? Small, limited seating. Food took WAY TOO long for what it is (i.e. onion rings). Beer is beer. Service was bad - bartender had an attitude and was pretty good at ignoring cutomers.
Great music, good atmosphere
Fun
Great spot to watch ACC action. If you are thinking about watching SEC or Big Ten action GTFO

Recently became quite the Duke fan since I completed a certificate from there. Couldn't really find a good place to catch a game though as most sports bars are geared towards the Big 10. Thought this was quite a fresh concept to push towards the ACC conf. and pay homage to the Duke UNC rivalry. Good vibes from this place. Seems heavily Duke fan populated from the multiple visits so far can't complain ! Seating  fills up quick so plan to get there slightly early for the big games. Food is legitimately authentic Southern I can attest to that from living in Bama for a number of years. They got there fried chicken and fried pickles down to perfection. Deep. Fried. Oreos. Boomshakalaka like Zion ! Staff is pretty chill and attentive, they got some good arcade fun in the back with some  hoop action 🏀. Gotta try the brunch next and see this place when Duke & UNC play will update.
Good place to get a drink!
(Translated by Google) This is very good the anviente is great the sexcelent drinks .. I recommend them  (Original) Esta buenisimo el anviente esta genial los trago sexcelentes .. los recomiendo
This is a place that sells North Carolina but doesn't even have Texas Pete.

Very limited seating. Service seems slow and is non-existent if you're standing (i.e. not sitting at a table or at the bar). I went for a trivia night and the trivia part was pretty fun and interesting but I basically stood the whole night and the one waitress I saw serving the tables around where I was standing didn't bother asking if I wanted anything
Great place to watch the game!
Definitely a college bar but if you come early in the afternoon should be pretty peaceful
Horrible experience to say the least. Many better bars in area. Food and drinks were not good, and bad treatment from management.
The AC barely works in the back room, and the food is ehh. It's a cool theme and the decor is extremely nice, but the actual food and drinks could be much better
Came here to celebrate my 21st birthday. I had lots of fun! The dj on the second floor plays good music 🔥 👍🏽
Lots of fun but did get super crowded. The new DJ was great.
Fun and girls

So I would have to say this place has good food and decent drink selection but what sets this place apart is the customer service our server BK was ridiculously helpful and cordial if I came back to Chicago it would be to visit here against I was extremely Pleasantly Surprised by this place I recommend it to anyone looking for a great experience in dining and drinking
Prices on drinks very high. You can drink at halligan bar for 1/4 of the price.
Karaoke Saturday nights 🤟🏼

Live music, places to charge a phone, and bar next door provides spotty free WiFi. I'll give them 3 stars.  Beer prices not listed so be prepared for them to charge you what they feel u can afford? As a poor looking single male, I've been here over an hour and still haven't been served.  At least my phone is charging up while I enjoy some free music and wifi. 3 stars for that ;) cheers
Games and beers!!
Not gonna lie, went to see a friend DJ vibes was actually great so I'll be back again.
Mechanical Bull riding on Friday's
Great place
music was trash. I was bored

NOT a good place to watch an ACC game!  On game nights, you have to pay to get any seat, not just at a table but at the bar too.  So, in order to sit, we were told that we had to pay $50 per seat to watch the game (even after the game had started).  I will not be returning.
Poor service, terrible rip-off in terms of quality of food and drink. Even after addressing with the manager, we left with a bad taste in our mouth. Will not return.

Went here for a wristband deal and everything was awesome but the manager was just a b****.. I asked to talk to her and she never wanted to come out, it took 3 times asking. In the end our party was satisfied and taken care of, shuffle board is lots of fun, and TVs everywhere for all your sports needs
Good fries
Nice spot!

Great atmosphere, really fun trivia. Wings and fries were just ok 6/10, the servers/bartenders were very busy and overwhelmed by the looks of it. But the price is right for beers on those specials nights!
Poor service. Nachos were great, everything else was meh
This is the place for great vibes and people. Drinks are good too but that's expected.
They were out of wine from the party the day before, which was a tuesday. We went on Wednesday, Halloween, and they only had cab and Chardonnay left.
Pleas turn down the tv sound during comercials, Just put music on.

I visited this place for the first time last night and my girls and I had the nastiest bartender and food. My purpose for visiting was for my friend’s performance. We enjoyed everything, but the service received from this lady working last night. We politely/patiently stood at the bar out of the way of everyone until we could order drinks. I understand the hustle, but she wasn’t serving anyone as we were waiting to be served—she just stood there.  We ordered shots and food and served ourselves with going back and forth to order drinks and food. When I asked for bbq sauce, she said it had to come from the kitchen as if I was supposed to go back there myself, I would’ve if I had known she would charge me for dipping sauce that I didn’t receive. Terrible service/ first impression. Maybe she was having a bad night, but I didn’t allow her  poor service to keep me from tipping after asking her what she thought her tip should be.
Mechanical bull was a blast and drinks were cheap.

The wings are awesome, the service is awesome, the atmosphere is awesome! I came in last min on a sunday night to finish some work on my laptop before I got home and was pleasantly surprised to find great spot that I'll surely return to! Despite the games going on, the staff was very attentive to my needs, despite me being huddled in a corner with my work. I'll be back soon!
Bottomless mimosas, big screen tvs, and chicken fried chicken. What else do you want?
Nice bar friendly people
Great TV's for sports. Great wings and burgers. Love it here!
Well made drinks and free popcorn!
One of my favorite bars in Chicago to watch sports. The TVs are huge. Excellent choices in beers too

Great place to socialize listen meet new friendly people. Bartenders are awesome and food is delicious especially Wednesday 50 cent wings & $5 pint Miller lite pitcher & $4 whiskey u can't beat it. And they have 2nd level karokee on Sundays and greet music thru out the week... Come on in meet new friend....
They have good cheese sticks and put up with you when you drink too much...

This bar was incredible, they worked with our organization to allow us the upstairs area for a large event. It went incredibly and they provided us with quite a few free drinks. They helped set it up in an incredibly rave like fashion and couldn't have been better.
It's alright lots of college kids

Usually I’ll judge a restaurant by the quality of their chicken tenders. In this case, this place has to get AAA’s because they actually read real check in and serve it to you so well. The stuff is so juicy and it falls apart in your mouth. But then there’s that perfect crisp on the outside that gives it a good dynamic labor. At the end the day damn good chicken tenders

I came here for a private event and the staff was truly unbelievably rude. They openly sexually harassed young women, and threw them out when they complained. Completely disgusting, sexist, abuse of power.
Great bar for sports and bar food. Beer list isn't that impressive, but the ACC themed menu is unique. Louisville hot brown is delicious.
Great food, nice selection of beer and great service. Me new go to sports bar here in Chicago #JustSayin
Great venue! (Upstairs)
Place is fine for what it is but warning this is NOT a Carolina bar. Infested with duke fans and the wait staff & everyone wears duke stuff. Will not be returning for any Carolina games.
The owner is a badass
Get the crispy ribs
Fun time fun night
Great food! Prices are not bad!

This sports restaurant/bar was one of the only places open on Columbus Day. The waitress was really nice, and offered us some beer specials. The food should improve. I found my burger boring, so I decided to eat only a half. I liked my Mac & cheese side. Overall, we had a good time. Being a Duke alumna I felt nostalgic in this place. I loved the poster with NC cities including my beloved Durham.
When I was there, half of the food menu was crossed off.  Service was pretty lack luster.  The decor does seem pretty ideal for watching sports though as there isn't a bad seat in the house.
Used to love this place but last trip service was really rough and the wings were cold inside...
Great place! Being from South Carolina, it was like being at home to watch Clemson play! The owner, Kyle is an awesome guy. He came over a greeted us and made us Southerners feel very welcome!
Love this place!  Great food, great service and the vibe is perfect.  Sports downstairs, dancing upstairs.
Trendy spot!
no cover, shot girls walking around with free shots, and got a booth quickly

The owner and staff we're very friendly. The food was amazing and very reasonably priced. Every game of every sport you could want was on one of the TVs and if that wasn't enough, there was skee ball and shuffle board.
Always have a great time here. Food is good. Staff is great!! Heather and Renee are fabulous!!!
Will H and Elizabeth were fabulous. Really friendly and accommodating, and knew their stuff. Food was great. Thanks for a great jest time in Chicago!

Kyle, the owner, has been focused on creating a neighborhood pub - not just another LP bar - and he's doing a great job.  Their breakfasts are great (huge portions) and they have a good selection of beer on tap.
Drinks aren't crazy expensive the bars theme is confusing?

I tried this place for their Tuesday $1 burger, 50 cent 6oz draft night..... Worth it! A half pound burger for a buck is a steal, and it was good. All the fixings will cost your extra. All in all a burger, fries and a beers ran me $5 before tip. I'll be back. Cool, clean alley sports bar. It was empty on a Tuesday though they still felt the need to start blasting music at 9pm which made it difficult to speak study my friend. This isn't a club, just a bar. So I'll come early to this bar unless you like the overly loud music.
Great deals and service

TR is the new hot spot in Lincoln Park. I had a great overall experience.  The food was incredible, the staff was friendly and provided great service, and the music was on point.  I would describe TR as an excellent place to grab a meal while watching the games. It's good for both family and friends. The night scene is fun too! The place has more 80 inch flat screen TVs than any other sports bar I've been to in Chicago. It's easy viewing for every angle.  The owner Kyle Siver did a great job with the place, and he went out of his way to make sure my friends and I were having a good time.  Can't wait to go back and try the ribs!

As a local restaurant owner and local foodie, Tobacco Road has some of the most underrated food in Lincoln Park. The bar food stands up against anyone in the city, everything is homemade and very fresh. I could not think of a better place to relax and watch sports. With all of the bars in the area this one stands out for its service, ambiance and amazing food.
Awesome, clean atmosphere with tons of space, great food, and an incredibly personable crew.

This place is great.  It's by far my favorite place to have a nice Sunday morning with great brunch food and the best Bloody Mary's in the city!  Waitresses are so beautiful and was surprised that the Chef came out to see how I liked my food, that was awesome. Thursday's $5.00 burgers made this a go to spot to take the kids for dinner before it got to busy too! This place gets added to my weekly routine, thanks for having me Tobacco Road.  :sunglasses:
Tuesday breakfast, had steak and eggs, price was $17, I found the steak to be prepared perfectly and very tender. Thought it was a good value. Will go back!!
Great environment, bar staff needs to work on their knowledge of the beer list...
Beer selection was okay, waitress didn't know anything about the beers, great place to watch a game.
Great spot. Bartenders are incredibly friendly, good beer and liquor selection. Shuffleboard, skee-ball, and Pop-a-Shot in the back. Great food menu too!
Great place to watch a game. Food is fantastic! The Chef even came to our table to chat, definitely worth checking this place out!
Great place to watch ACC sports. Each school is represented with memorabilia and special food items on the menu. Feels like home in Chicago. Goooo Jackets!
